<subSubSection id="D2CB657DFFBDC942FF062837FF06F92A" pageId="1" pageNumber="332" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="9A6E36F6FFBDC942FF062837FF06F92A" blockId="1.[151,756,1647,1735]" pageId="1" pageNumber="332">
<emphasis id="A8A5EAE4FFBDC942FF062837FEF0F965" bold="true" box="[151,283,1648,1672]" pageId="1" pageNumber="332">Etymology:</emphasis>
The specific name is a noun in apposition referring to the mountain range in which lies the 
<typeStatus id="456A8854FFBDC942FD5728D6FD1FF944" box="[710,756,1681,1705]" pageId="1" pageNumber="332">type</typeStatus>
locality.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="D2CB657DFFBDC941FF0628A7FE5DFE74" lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="333" pageId="1" pageNumber="332" type="description">
<paragraph id="9A6E36F6FFBDC942FF0628A7FABAF840" blockId="1.[151,757,1760,2078]" lastBlockId="1.[831,1437,1647,1996]" pageId="1" pageNumber="332">
<emphasis id="A8A5EAE4FFBDC942FF0628A7FEC3F91A" bold="true" box="[151,296,1760,1783]" pageId="1" pageNumber="332">Description:</emphasis>
<emphasis id="A8A5EAE4FFBDC942FEAC28A7FE11F91A" box="[317,506,1760,1783]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="332">
Male (
<typeStatus id="456A8854FFBDC942FE0328A7FE19F91A" box="[402,498,1760,1783]" pageId="1" pageNumber="332">holotype</typeStatus>
)
</emphasis>
. Total length 1.80. Carapace 0.85 long, 0.60 wide, pale greyish brown. Cephalic part of carapace somewhat elevated and protruded forward as shown in 
<figureCitation id="02EA2A73FFBDC942FD992905FDA4F8B6" box="[520,591,1858,1883]" captionStart="Figs 1 - 7" captionStartId="1.[151,192,1473,1494]" captionTargetBox="[156,1432,257,1378]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[147,1432,249,1404]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="Figs 1 - 7. Oedothorax khasi sp. nov., holotype. (1) Carapace, lateral view. (2) Distal part of right palp, retrolateral view. (3 - 4) Palpal tibia, dorsal and retrodorsal view, respectively. (5) Paracymbium. (6) Distal suprategular apophysis and embolic division, retrolateral view. (7) Embolic division, prolateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3098125/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="332">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
. Eyes slightly enlarged. Chelicerae 0.33 long, unmodified. Legs pale brown. Leg I 3.46 long (0.93+0.25+0.85+0.78+0.65), IV 3.22 long (0.88+0.23+0.83+0.80+0.48). Chaetotaxy 2.2.1.1, length of spines about 1.5 times diameter of segment. All metatarsi with a trichobothrium. TmI 0.63. Palp (
<figureCitation id="02EA2A73FFBDC942FEB32641FE62F7F3" box="[290,393,2054,2078]" captionStart="Figs 1 - 7" captionStartId="1.[151,192,1473,1494]" captionTargetBox="[156,1432,257,1378]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[147,1432,249,1404]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="Figs 1 - 7. Oedothorax khasi sp. nov., holotype. (1) Carapace, lateral view. (2) Distal part of right palp, retrolateral view. (3 - 4) Palpal tibia, dorsal and retrodorsal view, respectively. (5) Paracymbium. (6) Distal suprategular apophysis and embolic division, retrolateral view. (7) Embolic division, prolateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3098125/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="332">Figs 2-7</figureCitation>
): Tibia carrying a wide dorsal apophysis with a small invagination apically and two small tubercles retrolaterally. Paracymbium somewhat L-shaped. Distal surface of tegulum membranous. Distal suprategular apophysis short, wide, rounded distally. Embolus very short, radix relatively large, cylindrical, with a fold on its exterior surface. Convector with a wide lateral extention and a short, pointed distal apophysis. Main body of convector long, tapering posteriorly. Abdomen 1.15 long, 0.63 wide, dorsally pale, with an indistinct grey herring-bone pattern.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="9A6E36F6FFBDC942FCAE29F2FBE6F821" blockId="1.[831,1437,1647,1996]" box="[831,1037,1973,1996]" pageId="1" pageNumber="332">
<emphasis id="A8A5EAE4FFBDC942FCAE29F2FC7CF821" box="[831,919,1973,1996]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="332">Female.</emphasis>
Unknown.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="9A6E36F6FFBDC941FCAE29A2FE5DFE74" blockId="1.[831,1437,2021,2078]" lastBlockId="2.[151,756,258,410]" lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="333" pageId="1" pageNumber="332">
<emphasis id="A8A5EAE4FFBDC942FCAE29A2FBD4F813" bold="true" box="[831,1087,2021,2046]" pageId="1" pageNumber="332">Taxonomic remarks:</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="5DD14D75FFBDC942FBC529A2FACEF811" authority="Andrei V. Tanasevitch, 2017" authorityName="Andrei V. Tanasevitch" authorityYear="2017" box="[1108,1317,2021,2044]" class="Arachnida" family="Linyphiidae" genus="Oedothorax" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="1" pageNumber="332" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="khasi" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="A8A5EAE4FFBDC942FBC529A2FACEF811" box="[1108,1317,2021,2044]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="332">Oedothorax khasi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="B396579FFFBDC942FAAB29A1FA76F810" box="[1338,1437,2022,2045]" pageId="1" pageNumber="332" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
is similar to another Oriental species, 
<taxonomicName id="5DD14D75FFBDC942FA962640FA7DF7F3" authorityName="Tanasevitch" authorityYear="2017" box="[1287,1430,2055,2078]" class="Arachnida" family="Linyphiidae" genus="Oedothorax" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="1" pageNumber="332" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="myanmar">
<emphasis id="A8A5EAE4FFBDC942FA962640FAF1F7F3" box="[1287,1306,2055,2078]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="332">O</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="A8A5EAE4FFBDC942FAA12640FA7DF7F3" box="[1328,1430,2055,2078]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="332">myanmar</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, recently described from mountains of the Chin State in Myanmar (
<bibRefCitation id="FE404B07FFBEC941FEAF2F65FDF8FED6" author="Tanasevitch A. V." box="[318,531,290,315]" journalOrPublisher="Revue suisse de Zoologie" pageId="2" pageNumber="333" pagination="141 - 155" part="1" refString="Tanasevitch A. V. 2017. New genera and new species of the family Linyphiidae from Borneo, Sumatra and Java (Arachnida, Araneae). Revue suisse de Zoologie 124 (1): 141 - 155." title="New genera and new species of the family Linyphiidae from Borneo, Sumatra and Java (Arachnida, Araneae)" type="journal article" year="2017">Tanasevitch, 2017</bibRefCitation>
). The new species is clearly distinguished by the shape of the dorsal apophysis on the palpal tibia, as well as by the relatively large and not curved radix.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="D2CB657DFFBEC941FF062FF6FEDDFE05" pageId="2" pageNumber="333" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="9A6E36F6FFBEC941FF062FF6FEDDFE05" blockId="2.[151,756,433,488]" pageId="2" pageNumber="333">
